    • Method Detail

      • build

        <B> B build(Function<JFXAnimationTemplate<N>,B> builderFunction,
            Function<JFXTemplateBuilder.JFXAnimationObjectMapBuilder<N>,JFXTemplateBuilder.JFXAnimationObjectMapBuilder<N>> mapBuilderFunction)
        Method which handles a specific builderFunction which provides the JFXAnimationTemplate and should return a specific representation of the animation e.g. a Timeline.
        Furthermore the method provides a Function which provides a JFXTemplateBuilder.JFXAnimationObjectMapBuilder for defining the default animation objects and/or named animation objects.
        Type Parameters:
        B - the specific animation representation type.
        Parameters:
        builderFunction - the builderFunction for a specific representation of the animation.
        mapBuilderFunction - the builderFunction for defining the default animation objects and/or named animation objects.
        Returns:
        the specific animation representation.

      • build

        Timeline build()
        Same method as build(Object) )} but takes no default animation object.
        If you don't need a default animation object choose this method.
        In any case the default animation object will be null.
        Returns:
        the animation as Timeline instance.
